Static assets (CSS, JS, images) served under /static.

The JS files listed in base.html (js/lookup.js, js/picker.js, …) are
concatenated by Flask-Assets into a single gen/packed.js. Because they are
joined without separators, every bundled JS file MUST start with a leading
semicolon (;) — otherwise the last expression of the previous file and the
first of the next merge into one broken statement (ASI does not save you).
